quran[31]{c,v,t}:
  76,1,Has there not passed over man a period of time when he was nothing- -not even mentioned
  76,2,"Indeed, We have created man from the sperm drop, so that We may test him. Therefore, We gave him the faculties of hearing and sight"
  76,3,"Then We guided him to the Way: either to be grateful or to be a disbeliever"
  76,4,"For the disbelievers, We have prepared chains, fetters and a blazing fire"
  76,5,The righteous shall be in paradise drinking from a cup of wine mixed with Kafoor (camphorwater)
  76,6,"from a gushing spring at which the servants of Allah will refresh themselves, and shall be able to take out its channels from place to place at their will"
  76,7,They are those who keep their vows and dread the Day of widespread terror
  76,8,"who feed the poor, the orphan and the captive for the love of Allah"
  76,9,"saying: \"We feed you for the sake of Allah Alone; we seek from you neither reward nor thanks"
  76,10,for we dread from our Lord's torment of a very distressful Day
  76,11,"So Allah will deliver them from the evil of that Day, and bestow on them freshness and joy"
  76,12,"and reward them, for their steadfastness with paradise and garments of silk"
  76,13,There they shall be reclining upon high couches; they shall feel neither the scorching heat nor the biting cold
  76,14,"The trees of paradise will spread their shade around them, and their fruits will hang in clusters within their easy reach"
  76,15,"They shall be served with silver dishes, goblets of crystal"
  76,16,"and goblets made of crystal-clear silver, filled by their attendants in due measure"
  76,17,And they will also be given to drink a cup of wine mixed with Zanjabil (ginger-flavored water)
  76,18,"from a fountain, called Salsabil"
  76,19,"They shall be attended by boys graced with eternal youth: when you see them, they would seem like sprinkled pearls"
  76,20,"And which ever direction you will look, you will see blessings and the splendor of a great Kingdom"
  76,21,"They (the residents of paradise) shall be arrayed in the garments of fine green silk and rich brocade, and adorned with bracelets of silver, and their Lord will give them pure wine to drink"
  76,22,"O believers, that’s how you will be rewarded, and your endeavors appreciated"
  76,23,"Surely, it is We Who have sent down this Qur’an to you through gradual revelations"
  76,24,"therefore, await with patience the command of your Lord and do not yield to any sinner or disbeliever from among the unbelievers"
  76,25,Glorify the name of your Lord morning and evening
  76,26,prostrate before Him at night and glorify Him during the long hours of night
  76,27,These unbelievers love the transitory life of this world and neglect the heavy Day that is coming ahead
  76,28,It is We Who created them and made their joints strong; but if We please We can replace them with others like them through a change
  76,29,"This is indeed an admonition, so let him who will, adopt The Way to his Lord"
  76,30,"but you cannot will, except by the will of Allah. Surely Allah is All-Knowledgeable, All-Wise"
  76,31,"He admits to His mercy whom He wills, and for the wrongdoers He has prepared a painful punishment"